{"lemma":"قَبَضاتُ","slug":"قَبَضاتُ","root":"ق.ب.ض","root_slug":"ق-ب-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قَبْضَة","root":"قبض","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35092","n35101","n35102","n35103"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fist"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grasp"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handful"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"qabda (a linear measure of 12.5 cm)","tags":["Egypt"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"handle"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun of قَبَضَ (qabaḍa, “to grasp”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35092","headword_ar":"قَبَضَهُ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu biyadihi","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ بِيَدِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took it with his hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by actual touch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he closed his hand upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he grasped it; griped it; clutched it; seized it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took it with the whole of his hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, xx. 96:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aja*ahu","text_ar":"اَجَذَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took it"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any manner:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took it with his hand: he took possession of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he received it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, Mgh, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa Ealayohi","text_ar":"قَبَضَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa Ealayohi biyadahi","text_ar":"قَبَضَ عَلَيْهِ بِيَدَهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he grasped it, clutched it, laid hold upon it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seized it, with his hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amosakahu","text_ar":"اَمْسَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he seized it"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoHaY Ealayohi","text_ar":"اَنْحَى عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the whole of his hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracted, his fingers upon it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) it is also said, by MF, that some assert"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to signify the “ taking with the ends of the fingers; ” but this is a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA [in which it is said, in another place in this art., that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqobiyDN","text_ar":"تَقْبِيضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has also this last signification; but this is evidently, in like manner, a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqobiyDN","text_ar":"تَقْبِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa AlmataAEa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ المَتَاعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, the commodity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the commodities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa minohu Ald~ayona","text_ar":"قَبَضَ مِنْهُ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received, from him the debt"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qDY","text_ar":"قضى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.). And it is said in the Kur, [xx. 96,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faqabaDotu qaboDapF mino A^avari Alr~asuwli","text_ar":"فَقَبَضْتُ قَبْضَةً مِنْ اَثَرِ الرَّسُولِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and, accord. to an extraordinary reading, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyDapF","text_ar":"قَبِيضَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (B,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I took a handful"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the dust"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the footstep"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the hoof of the horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the messenger"},{"kind":"text","text":"[Gabriel]: (IJ, M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqotabaDa","text_ar":"اـِقْتَبَضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2482},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^atarihi qaboDapF","text_ar":"مِنْ اَتَرِهِ قَبْضَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaSa","text_ar":"قَبَصَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] is [said to be] a dial. form thereof. (TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa AlT~aAy^ira","text_ar":"قَبَضَ الطَّايِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He collected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprehended, the bird in his grasp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa EalaY Eurofi Alfarasi","text_ar":"قَبَضَ عَلَى عُرْفِ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grasped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid hold upon, the mane of the horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b2-  It is also used metaphorically, to denote the having an absolute property in a thing, to dispose of it at pleasure, without respect to the hand; as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDotu AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"قَبَضْتُ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAra","text_ar":"الدَّارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"got, possession of the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the house."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And [in like manner] it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqobiDu A@ll~`hu AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"يَقْبِضُ ا@للّٰهُ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaA='a","text_ar":"السَّمَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God will comprehend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collect together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"within his sole possession,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboDapN","text_ar":"قُبْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heaven."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [In like manner] you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa EalaY gariymihi","text_ar":"قَبَضَ عَلَى غَرِيمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He arrested his debtor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense in the present day]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa A@ll~`hu ruwHahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَ ا@للّٰهُ رُوحَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God took his soul."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God caused him to die."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qubiDa","text_ar":"قُبِضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, M, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S M, A, * K:) and also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a sick man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was at the point of death; in the state of having his soul taken; in the agony of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDotuhu Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"قَبَضْتُهُ عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I removed him from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, (M, K,) and so the inf. n., (S, M, Mgh,) also signifies the (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * M, Mgh, * K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qb~Dhu","text_ar":"قبّضهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqobiyDN","text_ar":"تَقْبِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [As such, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contracted it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drew it together."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa rijolahu wabasaTahaA","text_ar":"قَبَضَ رِجْلَهُ وَبَسَطَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contracted his leg, and extended it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa kaf~ahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَ كَفَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clenched his hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, Mgh, Msb, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brjm","text_ar":"برجم"},{"kind":"text","text":".). And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa yadahu Eanohu","text_ar":"قَبَضَ يَدَهُ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drew in his hand from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he refrained from laying hold upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Whence the saying in the Kur, [ix. 68,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayaqobiDuwna A^ayodiyahumo","text_ar":"وَيَقْبِضُونَ اَيْدِيَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they draw in their hands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refrain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] from expenditure, or from paying the [poor-rate called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaAp","text_ar":"زَكَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHahu","text_ar":"جَنَاحَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qb~D","text_ar":"قبّض","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracted his wing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAHahu","text_ar":"جَنَاحَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he contracted his wing to fly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above; (S, K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabuDa","text_ar":"قَبُضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) [or both;] inf. n. [of the former]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) and [of the latter, as indicated in the M,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaADapN","text_ar":"قَبَاضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaADN","text_ar":"قَبَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird, S, K, and a horse, A, and a man, S, or other [animal], K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in going"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqobiDona","text_ar":"يَقْبِضْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of birds, in the Kur, [lxvii. 19,] is [said to be] an ex. of this signification. (S, K. *) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"قَبَضَتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels were quick in their pace; at every spring therein, putting their legs together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inoqabaDa","text_ar":"اـِنْقَبَضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a company of men, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeyed, and was quick."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY fulaAnN","text_ar":"فِى فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inoqabaDa","text_ar":"اـِنْقَبَضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjatihi","text_ar":"حَاجَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one was quick, and light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, in accomplishing his want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazowN","text_ar":"نَزْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [Also, as contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He collected it together."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az.) And hence, (Az,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa AlA_ibila","text_ar":"قَبَضَ الاـِبِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, M) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He drove"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camels violently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"roughly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, M.) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) because the driver collects them together, when he desires to drive them; for when they disperse themselves from him, the driving of them is difficult: (Az, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inoqabaDa","text_ar":"اـِنْقَبَضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same, or, agreeably with an explanation given above, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went quickly with them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayoru yaqobiDu EaAnatahu","text_ar":"العَيْرُ يَقْبِضُ عَانَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The he-ass drives away his she-ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-  [As such also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qb~Dhu","text_ar":"قبّضهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqobiyDN","text_ar":"تَقْبِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, drew it, collected it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gathered it, together; contracted it, shrank it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrinkled it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, * K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa wajohahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَ وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, contracted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrinkled, his face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDati","text_ar":"قَبَضَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAru Aljilodapa","text_ar":"النَّارُ الجِلْدَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fire contracted, shrank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrivelled, the piece of skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~aDa","text_ar":"قَبَّضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bayoni Eayonayohi","text_ar":"مَا بَيْنِ عَيْنَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contracted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrinkled, the part between his eyes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN yuqab~iDu","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ يُقَبِّضُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bayona AlEayonayoni","text_ar":"مَا بَيْنَ العَيْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day that contracts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrinkles, the part between the eyes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; a metonymical phrase, denoting vehemence of fear, or of war. (M, TA. *) And in like manner you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHa$aY","text_ar":"الحَشَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN yuqab~iDu","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ يُقَبِّضُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day that contracts the bowels"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) [And hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as first mentioned, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a medicine, or food, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"astringed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constipated."},{"kind":"text","text":"And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(food)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was astringent"},{"kind":"text","text":"in taste; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqab~aDa","text_ar":"تَقَبَّضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b6-  As such also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He straitened it; scanted it; made it scanty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDa A@ll~`hu Alrizoqa","text_ar":"قَبَضَ ا@للّٰهُ الرِزْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as first mentioned, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God straitened, scanted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made scanty, the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And it is said in the Kur, [ii. 246,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@ll~`hu yaqobiDu wayabosuTu","text_ar":"وَا@للّٰهُ يَقْبِضُ وَيَبْسُطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And God straitens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makes scanty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the means of subsistence, to some, (Bd, Msb, * TA, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withholds"},{"kind":"text","text":"the means of subsistence from whom He will, (Jel,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and amplifies, enlarges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"makes ample"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the same, (Bd, Msb, Jel, TA,) to some, (Bd, TA,) or to whom He will. (Jel.) ―         -b7-  [As such also, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abridged his liberty."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yabosuTu gabiydahu vum~a yaqobiDuhumo","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَبْسُطُ غَبِيدَهُ ثُمَّ يَقْبِضُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one enlarges the liberty of his slaves; then abridges their liberty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b8-  [As such also, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, contracted his heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressed him; grieved him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu yaqobiDuniY maA yaqobiDuka","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ يَقْبِضُنِى مَا يَقْبِضُكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayabosuTuniY maA yabosuTuka","text_ar":"وَيَبْسُطُنِى مَا يَبْسُطُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily what distresses thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grieves thee, distresses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grieves, me; and what rejoices thee rejoices me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) [And it is related in a trad., that Mohammad said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faATimapu min~iY","text_ar":"فَاطِمَةُ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqobiDuniY maA qabaDahaA wayabosuTuniY maA basaTahAa","text_ar":"يَقْبِضُنِى مَا قَبَضَهَا وَيَبْسُطُنِى مَا بَسَطَهاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fátimeh is"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though she were a part"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of me: what hath distressed her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grieved her, distresses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grieves, me; and what hath rejoiced her rejoices me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Or the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu layaqobiDuniY maA qabaDaka","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيَقْبِضُنِى مَا قَبَضَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Lth, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily what hath annoyed and angered thee annoys and angers me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTN","text_ar":"بَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are terms applied by the investigators of truth among the Soofees to two contrary states of the heart, from both of which it is seldom or never free: the former being an affection of the heart withholding it from dilatation and joy; whether the cause thereof be known, as the remembrance of a sin or an offence, or of an omission, or be not known; and some of them make other divisions thereof. (TA.) [In like manner] you say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~aA famaA qabaDaka","text_ar":"عَنَّا فَمَا قَبَضَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoqabaDotu","text_ar":"اِنْقَبَضْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou shrankest from us: and what made thee to shrink?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b9-  [As such also, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made him close-fisted, tenacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardly."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayoru yaqobiDuhu waAl$~ar~u yabosuTuhu","text_ar":"الخَيْرُ يَقْبِضُهُ وَالشَّرُّ يَبْسُطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth makes him close-fisted, tenacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardly; and poverty makes him open-handed, liberal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","O","K","Lth","B","IJ","IAar","TA","Az","Jel","Bd"]},{"entry_id":"n35101","headword_ar":"قَبْضَةٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDaAtN","text_ar":"قَبَضَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places. ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboDapN","text_ar":"قُبْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqobiDN","text_ar":"مَقْبِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-  Also, [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure of a man's fist, from side to side;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four finger-breadths;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariybN","text_ar":"جَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sixth part of the common"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAE","text_ar":"ذِرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or cubit: but in the present day, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure of a man's fist with the thumb erect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is about"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six inches and a quarter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDaAtN","text_ar":"قَبَضَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb, vocibus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariybN","text_ar":"جَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n35102","headword_ar":"قُبْضَةٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A handful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what one takes with the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grasps;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh;) as, for instance,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino sawiyqK","text_ar":"مِنْ سَوِيقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of meal of parched barley"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino tamorK","text_ar":"مِنْ تَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of dates"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, A, Msb;) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~AF","text_ar":"كَفّاً"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDapN","text_ar":"قَبْضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, A, K;) but the former is the more common; (S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyDapN","text_ar":"قَبِيضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (B:) or the first is a subst. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqobuwDN","text_ar":"مَقْبُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the second is a n. un.: (TA:) the pl. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qubaDN","text_ar":"قُبَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaf~iY","text_ar":"كَفِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA qaboDapu","text_ar":"هٰذَا قَبْضَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the quantity that my hand grasps."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) See two other exs. of the second word, and an ex. of the third, in 1, before the first break in the paragraph. It is also said in the Kur, [xxxix. 67,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@loA^aroDu jamiyEFA","text_ar":"وَا@لْاَرْضُ جَمِيعًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma AlqiyaAmapi","text_ar":"يَوْمَ القِيَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDatuhu","text_ar":"قَبْضَتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboDatuhu","text_ar":"قُبْضَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDapN","text_ar":"قَبْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n. [of un.] used as a subst., or is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu qaboDapK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ قَبْضَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd,) and the literal signification is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the earth altogether shall be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his handful"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Bd, Jel;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his possession"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and at his free and absolute disposal:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) Th says, that this is like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~aAru fiY qaboDatiY","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّارُ فِى قَبْضَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning as explained above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this opinion is not valid:) (M:) another reading is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDatahu","text_ar":"قَبْضَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the accus. case, (M, Bd,) as an adv. n.; that which is determinate being thus likened to what is vague; (Bd;) and this is allowed by some of the grammarians; but it is not allowed by any one of the grammarians of El-Basrah. (M.) It is also said, in the trad. of Bilál and the dates,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajaEala yajiYo'u bihi qubaDFA qubaDFA","text_ar":"فَجَعَلَ يَجِىْءُ بِهِ قُبَضًا قُبَضًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he set about bringing them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the pronoun referring to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~amor","text_ar":"التَّمْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dates"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"handfuls by handfuls"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","B","TA","Bd","Jel","M"]},{"entry_id":"n35103","headword_ar":"قُبَضَةٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qubaDapN rufaDapN","text_ar":"قُبَضَةٌ رُفَضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, TA,) to this latter, not to the former alone, the following explanation applies, (TA,) A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who lays hold upon a thing, and then leaves it without delay."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K.) And the former, A pastor"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who draws his sheep or goats together, not going far and wide in pasturing them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who manages well"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his sheep or goats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for his beasts, collecting them together, and, when he finds a place of pasture, spreads them abroad:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and the latter, a pastor"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who manages well, and is gentle with his pasturing beasts, collecting them together and driving them, when their place of pasturage becomes wanting in herbage, and, when they light upon a piece of herbage, leaves them to spread abroad and pasture at pleasure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who collects together his camels, and drives them until he brings them whithersoever he will."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rfD","text_ar":"رفض"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","S","M","A","TA","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}